.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-decode 1  "decode " 
.SH NAME
decode \- Decode a WebP file to PNG (default), PPM/PAM, or raw pixels
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdecode\fR <\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR> [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-layout\fR] [\fB\-\-frames\fR] [\fB\-\-frame\fR] [\fB\-\-metadata\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIINPUT\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Decode a WebP file to PNG (default), PPM/PAM, or raw pixels
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output path; `\-` writes stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR
Output format; defaults to the `\-o` extension, else PNG
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
png: PNG, RGBA8
.IP \(bu 2
ppm: Netpbm binary PPM (`P6`, RGB; alpha dropped)
.IP \(bu 2
pam: Netpbm binary PAM (`P7`, RGBA)
.IP \(bu 2
bmp: BMP (RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
tiff: TIFF (RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
raw: Raw row\-major pixels in the requested `\-\-layout`
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-layout\fR \fI<LAYOUT>\fR [default: rgba8]
Byte order for raw output only
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
rgba8: `R, G, B, A`
.IP \(bu 2
argb8: `A, R, G, B`
.IP \(bu 2
bgra8: `B, G, R, A`
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-frames\fR \fI<FRAMES>\fR
For animations: which frames to emit
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
first: Only the first composited frame (the default)
.IP \(bu 2
all: Every composited frame, numbered `<stem>\-000.<ext>`, ...
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-frame\fR \fI<FRAME>\fR
For animations: emit only this 0\-based frame
.TP
\fB\-\-metadata\fR \fI<METADATA>\fR
Metadata to carry into the output: all,none,icc,exif,xmp (default: all)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
all: Keep ICC, Exif, and XMP
.IP \(bu 2
none: Strip everything (a bare `VP8L` output)
.IP \(bu 2
icc: Keep the ICC color profile
.IP \(bu 2
exif: Keep Exif
.IP \(bu 2
xmp: Keep XMP
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
[\fIINPUT\fR] [default: \-]
Input `.webp` file; `\-` (the default) reads stdin
